# [PIM](../wg/pim.html)

## Summary
The PIM Working Group meeting at IETF 125 focused on the progression of existing drafts toward publication, the adoption of new work related to SRv6 and Flex-Algo, and several new proposals addressing modern network architectures. Key highlights included a status update on the multi-year effort to revise RFC 1112, a proposal for native IPv4 multicast over IPv6-only cores, and discussions regarding the use of multicast for Large Language Model (LLM) synchronization. Interoperability results for BIER and MVPN were also presented.

